Vol / Page: Indulgence (supplement) / 20
Edition:
Quote: There are two species: Phorium tenax, also know as harakeke, whararahi or swamp flax; and phorium cookianum, also known as wharariki or mountain flax. ... Harakeke can be differentiated from wharariki by its larger size and seed pods.
